ence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]},{"name":"Isobel","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Isabel ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Isabel Wadeton was born about 1187, in Brixham, Torbay, Devon, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of William Wadeton. She married Martin Fishacre before 1217. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"Abt 1187–":"umbes 1187–Surnud","1187–Female":"1187–Surnud","1186–Male":"1186–Surnud","1215–Male":"1215–Surnud","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1165–Male":"1165–Surnud","1215":"1215","Abt 1187":"umbes 1187","Abt 1220":"umbes 1220","1165":"1165","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1186":"1186","before 1217":"enne 1217","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom",", , Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Morleigh, Totnes, Devon, England":"Brixham, Torbay, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1187–":"noin 1187–Kuollut","1187–Female":"1187–Kuollut","1186–Male":"1186–Kuollut","1215–Male":"1215–Kuollut","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1165–Male":"1165–Kuollut","1215":"1215","Abt 1187":"noin 1187","Abt 1220":"noin 1220","1165":"1165","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1186":"1186","before 1217":"ennen vuotta 1217","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta",", , Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Morleigh, Totnes, Devon, England":"Brixham, Torbay, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1187–":"environ 1187–Décédée","1187–Female":"1187–Décédée","1186–Male":"1186–Décédé","1215–Male":"1215–Décédé","1220–Male":"1220–Décédé","1165–Male":"1165–Décédé","1215":"1215","Abt 1187":"environ 1187","Abt 1220":"environ 1220","1165":"1165","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1186":"1186","bef